title: Domestic beer consumption in Canada by age group 2019
summary: In general Share of beer consumption has fallen over the Year.
Share of beer consumption is roughly constant from 35_to_49 to 50_to_64, and finally slightly decreasing from 50_to_64 to 65_and_over.
The most drastic decrease took place within the Year 50_to_64 and 65_and_over.
The highest Share of beer consumption, of value 29.9 was reached at Year 35_to_49
The lowest Share of beer consumption, of value 8.0 was reported at Year 65_and_over
